NLquery: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it.
prompt: You are an expert at writing SQL queries. Translate any natural language I give you into an SQL query. Natural language: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them. Return only a query with no explanation.
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT sid, version FROM ( SELECT sid, version, COUNT(*) AS version_count, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY sid ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC) AS rn FROM Base_Model GROUP BY sid, version ) AS RankedVersions WHERE rn = 1;

NLquery: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it.
prompt: You are an agent to translate natural language into an SQL query. Use these relevant schema tables to structure your response: ModelServices(bmid, sid, version) BaseModel(bmid, creator_uid, description). Return only the SQL query with no explanation. Natural language request: 'For each Internet Service (sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that use it. If multiple versions tie for highest frequency, return any one.'
LLM_returned_SQL_query: SELECT sid, version FROM ModelServices AS T1 WHERE T1.version = (SELECT T2.version FROM ModelServices AS T2 WHERE T1.sid = T2.sid GROUP BY T2.version ORDER BY COUNT(T2.version) DESC, T2.version ASC LIMIT 1) GROUP BY sid;

LLM_returned_SQL_query: WITH RankedVersions AS ( SELECT sid, version, COUNT(*) AS version_count, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY sid ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC) AS rn FROM ModelServices GROUP BY sid, version ) SELECT sid, version FROM RankedVersions WHERE rn = 1;
